The paper deals with Bayesian belief networks and approximating marginal probabilities, which are topics commonly studied in the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of heuristics and integer linear programming also suggests a focus on optimization and algorithms, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SI and cs.DS. Finally, the paper also touches on information theory (cs.IT) in its discussion of probability mass and the efficiency of approximations.
